  "prompt": "Will doing organic chemistry from Ncert enough for Neet 17?",
  "response": "For NEET 2017 and similar competitive exams, studying organic chemistry from NCERT textbooks is considered a good starting point. The NCERT books are specifically designed to cover the syllabus outlined by the National Eligibility cum Entrance Test (NEET) and are an essential resource for understanding basic concepts. \n\nHowever, while NCERT is crucial, it may not be sufficient on its own for scoring well in NEET due to the following reasons:\n\n1. **Depth of Understanding**: NEET questions can sometimes require a deeper understanding or application of concepts than what is covered in NCERT. Supplementing your study with additional reference books can help reinforce your knowledge.\n\n2. **Practice**: It\u2019s essential to practice a variety of problems and previous years' question papers to familiarize yourself with the exam format and question types.\n\n3. **Additional Resources**: Consider using other reference books such as \"Organic Chemistry\" by Morrison and Boyd or \"Organic Chemistry\" by Paula Bruice for a more in-depth understanding of organic chemistry.\n\n4. **Coaching Materials**: If you are enrolled in any coaching classes, their materials can also provide valuable insights and practice problems.\n\nIn summary, while NCERT is vital and should be thoroughly studied, combining it with additional resources and consistent practice will better prepare you for NEET.",
